  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute gastrointestinal bleeding is potentially lethal in liver cirrhosis. Accurate assessment&#xD;
      of prognosis is critical in a timely fashion. A novel model, CAGIB score, has been developed&#xD;
      based on our Chinese multicenter retrospective study. Now, a prospective, international&#xD;
      multicenter, observational study will be performed to further compare the performance of&#xD;
      CAGIB versus Child-Pugh and MELD scores for evaluating the in-hospital mortality of patients&#xD;
      with liver cirrhosis and acute gastrointestinal bleeding.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
